{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1778260927,"nonce":"gasL0px8GtslChI4DDRutgB/Zik=","title":"Bimodal-replicate analysis: cluster-conditioned Δv reporting across all training runs","message":"Prerequisite analysis for all stages in the proposed regulator-coupling / decoupling-chain programme (exploration, not committed). Addresses the risk that collapsing to group-mean Δv hides qualitatively different controller solutions.\n\n**Problem.** The current −25% group mean for trained flavor-B GRUs hides a bimodal replicate distribution: ~25% of replicates land at +40 to +57% Δv, the rest at −20 to −30%. This is documented in synthesis.md §7.1.1 and is incompatible with any clean structural prediction (e.g., Gemini's claim that flavor-B \"must\" give negative Δv fails for the +40% tail). Reporting group means throughout the programme would mask this bimodality.\n\n**Approach.**\n1. Cluster trained-controller replicates by final-loss strata or by Δv value distribution (k-means on scalar Δv, or Gaussian mixture on (final_loss, Δv) pairs).\n2. Report Δv conditioned on cluster for all current training runs. Apply to synthesis.md §7.1.1 data.\n3. For all future training stages (2–9), instrument the evaluation pipeline to produce cluster-conditioned Δv reports automatically, not just group means.\n4. Investigate what structural/training differences separate the two clusters (different local minima, different seed-induced symmetry breaking, early vs late convergence?).\n\n**Success criterion.** A reproducible clustering assignment for existing replicates; a pipeline hook that generates cluster-conditioned violin plots at evaluation time for all future runs.\n\n**Why this is an error.** Existing results in synthesis.md report a mean Δv that actively obscures the sign disagreement within the replicate population. Any downstream stage that uses the mean Δv as a scalar target is operationally broken.\n\n**Cross-refs.** synthesis.md §7.1.1. Plan §7 (bimodality risk). All training-method stages in the chain. Training-methods coord c99ad9d.","files":null}]}